JPM on Mphasis
OW, TP Rs 2650

See five main takeaways from the Analyst Day

1) AI implementation in brownfield projects remains complex as service providers need to have the context of the existing enterprise tech stack to implement AI solutions;

2) It launched AI platform Tria where the pricing will be in the form of a subscription fee, implementation fee and managed services;

3) It has invested in setting up a strategic engagement team for improving the “go to market” function with early success in expanding small transformation deals into multi-year ones with larger average large deal sizes;

4) It elaborated on its Balance Sheet an intensive strategy of “buying out” contracts from tail vendors as part of the vendor consolidation exercises and intends to do more such “buy outs”;

5) Mphasis is transitioning from a services led model to platform+outcome based model from FY27 and will start reporting new metrics from FY28 such as ARR, platform attach rate and net retention rate.
